# Design Guidelines (Mobile-First)

When editing **basestrike** UI (app, components, globals), follow [Base Mini App Design Guidelines](https://docs.base.org/mini-apps/featured-guidelines/design-guidelines). See `basestrike/docs/UX-RESEARCH.md` for full research.

## Layout

- Design for **small viewports** and **portrait orientation** first.
- Keep **core actions near top or middle** — not hidden behind scroll.
- Limit buttons; make the **first action obvious** (e.g. "Start Game", "Play").
- **Optimize for thumb reach and one-handed use.**

## Navigation

- Use a **bottom navigation bar** for primary tabs.
- **Always include labels under icons** for each tab.
- Test on multiple device sizes; ensure buttons are not cut off.
- Use `safe-area-pb` (or `env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`) for notched devices.

## Touch

- **All touch targets must be at least 44px** (min height or width, or padding so hit area ≥ 44px). Use e.g. `min-h-[44px]` or `min-h-11` (44px in Tailwind).
- Do **not** rely on **hover states** — use `:active` and tap feedback; touch screens have no hover.
- Support tap (and swipe/pinch where appropriate).

## Colors & Themes

- Use **semantic color tokens** (e.g. `--color-primary`, `--color-background`, `--color-foreground`) with light/dark overrides when possible.
- Support light and dark modes; respect system preference; allow manual toggle.
- Maintain contrast and brand consistency.

## Typography

- Prefer **Inter** for body text (Base recommendation).
- Ensure **sufficient contrast** between text and background.
- Use regular, bold, italic; reserve decorative/script fonts for accents only.

## Spacing

- Use a **base spacing unit** (4px or 8px) consistently (Tailwind: 4px base).
- Group related elements; give content room; avoid cramped layouts.

## Viewport

- Ensure viewport meta: `width=device-width, initial-scale=1`. For notched devices, consider `viewport-fit=cover` and safe-area insets.
